cience ls  at the university of california berkeley  she started her academic career at the university of san diego  received her phd in applied physics at stanford and did her undergraduate work at dartmouth research areas condensed matter experiment materials physics  physics of novel magnetic semiconducting and superconducting materials thin film growth techniques to prepare materials not available by bulk preparation techniques such as amorphous alloys multilayers or metastable materials development of nanocalorimetry for thin films small bulk samples appointments professor department of physics university of california berkeley date professor dept of materials science and engineering university of california berkeley date member materials sciences division lawrence berkeley national laboratory date assistant to full professor department of physics university of california san diego  postdoctoral member of technical staff att bell laboratories  degrees ba physics dartmouth college summa cum laude phi beta kappa with high honors in physics  phd applied physics stanford university  selected honors and awards aps keithley instrumentation award  fellow of the american physical society  member board on physics and astronomy  executive committee  member solid state sciences committee sssc  member decadal survey team cmmp   member of nsf advisory board mathematical and physical sciences  chair topical group on magnetism gmag of aps  member of executive committee  gmag program chair  chair division of materials physics dmp of aps  member of exec comm  member aps cswp committee on the status of women in physics  member aps popa panel on public affairs  chair doe division of materials science and engineering advisory council date community science boards san diego elementary institute of science san diego education fund san diego foundation science and technology working group uccosmos sf exploratorium selected recent significant professional activities selected recent si